                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d772">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.51/338.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Vice President of the Whitney Central Trust and Savings
                            Bank of New Orleans</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 18, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your telegram of the
                    8th instant, and your letter of the 11th of the same month, in regard to <pb
                        facs="0735" n="619" xml:id="pg_619"/> the proposed temporary loan of
                    $500,000 to Honduras, and begs to say in reply that it has already taken up the
                    matter to which you referred with Mr. Zemurray, who has doubtless already
                    advised you of the substance of the interview.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
